MG 54 Wellington Camacho  Think twice before booking this place... If I could give it a 0 I would. My cousins fiancé sat with one of the coordinators Wellington Camacho on March 2nd 2017 and booked May 28th 2017 for my baby shower... I submitted my deposit as requested via chase quick pay on March 6 and 15th... on March 25th I lost my cousin suddenly and our family has been mourning his loss since. Today April 21st my cousins fiancé contacted the coordinator to touch base with him when he informs her that they double booked May 28th and although arrangements were made with us first we were out on the venue. They never once called us even though they had my deposit for a month and half already. Had she not called him I would have never been informed of this and probably would have never know until the balance was due which is two weeks prior to your event as stated on my recent and text messages sent to me from the coordinator. When I called he told me he would work on resolving this issue. Never called me back just sent me my deposit no sorry no solution no options. I have spent money on invitations I have family traveling from all over and now will possibly not have my shower as I have been unable to find a location that isn't booked. This how they treat a woman 29 weeks pregnant. Let me not forget to mention my cousins fiancé is a returning costumer who had thrown his 30th birthday with them September 2016.
